<function>

access:   public

name: buildCreateTable

param: string, $name

param: string, $cols

return: mixed

</function>

Builds a CREATE TABLE statment.

* Parameters:

 * string //$name//: The table name to create.

 * string //$cols//: The column definitions.

* Returns mixed: An SQL-safe quoted value.

Builds a CREATE TABLE statment.

We use this so that certain drivers can append table types
to the creation statment (e.g. MySQL).